Vocals by James Meadows


V1
She had a candle on a cupcake
When she walked into the room
She told me “Happy Birthday”
“Dad I made this Just for you”
She had a picture of her momma
Taken just before she died
She gave me the cupcake
And sat down by my side

Chorus

She said “When you blow out the candle daddy
You can have one wish
Thats what momma told me
So I know thats how it is
I’ve been missin’ momma, Daddy
She’s been gone so long
So when you blow out the candle
Daddy please
Wish momma would come home

V2
I just sat there shakin’
As my eyes filled up with tears
And I wished with all my broken heart
Her momma could be here
How do you tell a little girl
Her momma’s really gone
and all the wishes in the world
Will never bring her home

Repeat Chorus

Bridge
I looked at the candle
And the picture in her hand
And I prayed for the words
To help her understand
I said momma’s gone to Heaven
But she’s always by your side
She’s just a wish away
And you can wish it anytime

2ND Chorus

Then we both blew out the candle
And we both made one wish
Thats not how momma said it works
But thats the way it is
And somewhere up in Heaven
Lord I’m sure her mom could see
A Candle on A cupcake
And an Angel on my knee
